&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a fixed-term Band 6 Uro-oncology Nurse Specialist &lt;strong&gt;to cover a 12-month Maternity Leave role.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a committed, enthusiastic and motivated person to join the urology nursing team. The successful applicant will be part of a well-established multi-disciplinary team working closely with the Urology Consultants, junior doctors and other Nurse Specialists within the department.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be expected to play an active part in supporting the quality of care and the experience of urology patients through clinical practice, nurse led clinics, education, research and audit.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will therefore need experience in urological nursing and to acquire substantial knowledge of the subject and will be fully supported to achieve this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will provide you with development opportunities and support you within your new role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you feel that you have the skills and dedication for these role please contact Paula Allchorne, Lead Urology Nurse 0208 535 6940 or email p.allchorne@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
